Heading Tags (h1-h6):

Definition: Heading tags are used to define headings or titles on a webpage. They range from <h1> (the highest level) to <h6> (the lowest level).
Example:
html
Copy code

<h1>This is a Heading 1</h1>
<h2>This is a Heading 2</h2>
...
<h6>This is a Heading 6</h6>
Paragraph Tag (p):

Definition: The <p> tag is used to define paragraphs of text.
Example:
html
Copy code

<p>This is a paragraph of text.</p>
Div Tag (div):

Definition: The <div> tag is a generic container that is used to group elements together.
Example:
html
Copy code

<div>
    <p>This is inside a div.</p>
    <p>Another paragraph inside the same div.</p>
</div>
Span Tag (span):

Definition: The <span> tag is an inline container that is used to apply styles to a specific portion of text.
Example:
html
Copy code

<p>This is <span style="color:red;">red</span> text.</p>
Line Break Tag (br):

Definition: The <br> tag is used to insert a line break within text.
Example:
html
Copy code

<p>This is the first line.<br>This is the second line.</p>
Various HTML Tags:

This includes tags like <a> for links, <img> for images, <input> for form inputs, <button> for buttons, etc.
Centering Content:

Use CSS styles like text-align: center; or <div style="text-align: center;">.
