Table Heading, Cellpadding, Cellspacing, Colspan, Rowspan, Table Backgrounds, Table Height and Width, Table Caption, Table Header, Body, Footer:

These are attributes and elements used within the <table> tag to structure and style tabular data. Examples:

html
Copy code

<table border="1" cellpadding="5" cellspacing="0" width="400">
  <caption>This is a table caption</caption>
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th colspan="2">Table Heading</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td rowspan="2">Row 1, Col 1</td>
      <td>Row 1, Col 2</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td>Row 2, Col 2</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
  <tfoot>
    <tr>
      <td colspan="2">Table Footer</td>
    </tr>
  </tfoot>
</table>
Lists - Ordered, Unordered, Nested, Definition:

Ordered List (ol): A list where each item is numbered. Example:
html
Copy code

