  <li>Item 1</li>
  <li>Item 2</li>
</ol>
Unordered List (ul): A list where each item is marked with a bullet point. Example:
html
Copy code
<ul>
  <li>Item 1</li>
  <li>Item 2</li>
</ul>
Nested List: Lists can be nested within each other.
Definition List (dl): A list of terms and their definitions. Example:
html
Copy code
<dl>
  <dt>Term 1</dt>
  <dd>Definition 1</dd>
  <dt>Term 2</dt>
  <dd>Definition 2</dd>
</dl>
These HTML elements and attributes are fundamental for structuring and styling content on web pages. Understanding how to use them effectively will allow you to create well-organized and visually appealing websites.
